UGREEN Guitar Cable 6.35mm 1/4 Inch TS Unbalanced Mono Cable Male Cord Compatible with Electric Guitar, Bass Guitar, Electric Mandolin, Pro Audio

UGREEN Gold Plated Premium 6.35mm Mono Jack 1/4" TS Cable is designed to connect instruments such as synths, keyboards, guitars and other professional audio equipment. It is made of Copper conductors for enhanced signal clarity, and ideal for studio or live performances.

Wide Compatibility

The 6.35mm to 6.35mm guitar lead instrument audio cable is fully compatible with devices equipped with standard 6.35mm 1/4" jack, such as electric bass guitar, synths, electric desktop keyboard, electric mandolin, classical acoustic guitars, Amplifier, speaker, patch, piano and other professional audio equipments

Amazing Sound Quality

With Oxygen-free copper and triple shielding, this dual 6.35mm to 3.5mm audio cable could provide maximum's conductivity and durability, and ensure a exceptional sound quality.

Multiple Interior Shielding

Oxygen free copper, triple shielding could increase the anti-interference ability, and ensure superior fidelity sound. Enhanced signal clarity and ideal for studio or live performances.

Specification

1. Connectors: 6.35mm 1/4" Mono Male x2;

2. Connect instruments such as synths, keyboards, guitars and other professional audio equipment;

3. Low noise resistance, for superior performance, perfect for digital or analog signals;

4. Copper provide maximum's conductivity and durability;

Package Contents

  • UGREEN Gold Plated Premium 6.35mm Mono Jack 1/4" TS Cable Unbalanced Guitar Patch Cords x1

24K Gold-Plated Connector

24K 15U Gold plated connectors resist corrosion and ensure optimum sound quality

Durable Nylon Braided 1/4 Inch Cable

Double layer nylon braid guards against harsh installs where the cable is tugged across sharp edges, protecting it from being scratched

Zinc Alloy Casing

Zinc alloy case prevents scratches and rust, more durable

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzes reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2020
      Size: 10FTVerified Purchase
      OK so this is a really cheap cable, so it wouldn't be right to expect the very best, (although, paying a fortune doesn't necessarily give you a superior cable...) but these are absolutely unusable! I have been a working guitarist for 30 years now, and I have NEVER come across a cable so microphonic (picks up physical noise -such as every time the cable moves or is touched). I've now read several reviews that I should have taken notice of before buying, but I thought how bad can a cable really be if it has a solid connection, copper wire and shielding, right? I hate to give bad reviews, especially for low-cost items, but this design is really not fit for purpose whatsoever.

      1.0 out of 5 stars Bad for pets, guitars, and amplifiers, possibly in that order.
      Reviewed in the United States on March 12, 2021
      Size: 6FTVerified Purchase
      This thing is abysmal. As countless others have mentioned, it is EXTREMELY microphonic. It will literally explode with unwanted sounds at the slightest touch. One time, my dog walked over it and a deafening pop burst from my amplifier that was somehow louder than the guitar itself.

      Until I replaced it, I didn't dare move a muscle while playing, lest the cord accidentally bump my leg or table, thereby causing a sudden noise that would freak out my dog, who would then run over the cable in fear, all of which culminating in my dog frantically chasing his tail atop the cable and machine-gunning the world with sad amp noises. Or angry amp noises. Your amp will be upset, is what I'm saying. As will your neighbors, nearby birds and squirrels, and that one FBI guy in the van across the street spying on you with a directional microphone (hi John!).

      Basically, unless you want to permanently traumatize your dog (or really stick it to the Feds), get a different cable.

      DannyBlue
      5.0 out of 5 stars I'd classify them as "home studio" grade
      Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2017
      Size: 3FTVerified Purchase
      Ugreen cables in general are great looking. Fantastic first impressions, and they feel very solid. Mine also shipped individually bagged, which I found quite unique; I've only ever bought cables from music stores, and those usually have less packaging put into them, so it was a nice surprise. The cables train well, and fairly quick from my experience (about a week to let them take on their new shape), and I haven't had much extra stiffness throughout the entire length after another week or so. Zero complaints on sound quality, but I'd say that's expected. Either way, sound quality is always good to note.

      Overall, I'd recommend them. I didn't look for too many alternatives, but for the price, definitely a cable I'll come back to for future purchases if the price point doesn't change, and I don't need a cheaper cable.
